# Project documentation (LSC Platform)

At session start (architecture or multi-file work): read **`docs/specs/ai-agent-preflight.md`** and recap §1–§6 for the human.

Before finishing any task that adds, changes, or removes features, infrastructure, or packages:

1. Read **`docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md`** and **`docs/ai/CONTEXT.md`** (session snapshot) for current state.
2. Update **`docs/CHANGELOG.md`** — new dated entry at the top (What / Why / Impact).
3. Update **`docs/PROJECT_STATUS.md`** — checkboxes, dates, next steps.
4. If roadmap phase changed, update **`docs/ROADMAP.md`**.
5. For non-trivial work, add one paragraph to **`docs/ai/MAINTAINER-NOTES.md`**.

**Source of truth:** `docs/*.md` in git. The public page **`/platform`** renders these files — do not duplicate content only in React components.

**Do not** put secrets in any `docs/` file. Reference env var names only.

Architecture details remain in **`.cursorrules`**, not duplicated into changelog prose.
